1 - Install Touchégg dependences:
    $ sudo apt-get install build-essential libqt4-dev utouch libx11-6 libxtst-dev

2 - Compile and install Touchégg:
    $ qmake
    $ make
    $ sudo make install

3 - Configure your device:
    http://code.google.com/p/touchegg/wiki/ConfigureDevices

4 - Run Touchégg:
    $ touchegg

5 - Make a gesture, for example drag two fingers over your trackpad. If all
    works fine, the name of the gesture will appear.

6 - To use your own configuration edit $HOME/.touchegg/touchegg.conf
    GUI in progress ;)
